comments.body:
We need to figure out the location code for numismatics. If we index them now with no change they will take https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/c5f851aea6e7c65306e17fb40ec9cf74c40a0a7f/app/resources/numismatics/coins/orangelight_coin_builder.rb#L142 location code `num`. 
In https://bibdata-alma-staging.princeton.edu/locations/holding_locations the location code for numismatics is `rare$num`.

The location code will need to be updated in figgy. We can't make this change, though, until we are ready to turn off syncing for the production catalog.

bibdata.title: Ensure non-recap holdings and items are excluded from scsb record dump

comments.body:
I also updated the description ^. We are looking for `852 | 8` to get the holding id and then to get the items attached to this holding we are looking for `876 | 0`. 

- Subfield `852 | b` and `852 | c` provide the location code that we will cross check with the locations table. 

- Another option is to have an array of location codes for the library name that indicates if it is a remote storage or not (recap_rmt). For example `firestone$pf`, `firestone$pb` we know that they are `recap_rmt`. 
In both options we need to maintain the code base with updated remote storage locations.

comments.body: @hackartisan are you asking me to keep one or the other?
I noticed that my test does not include the USE_ALMA maybe that created a confusion.

From slack @hackartisan explained to me that she meant to keep all the options for numismatics for more flexibility; I explained that the orangelight/alma branch includes the request version that is looking for rare$num; this will only work when it gets merged and we are in the alma environment. So it wouldn't work to index numismatics earlier with `rare$num` if we are not in alma mode.

[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/40132098/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/40132098)

Coverage remained the same at 96.726% when pulling **d583cbdf047a8d71e2bd5033c55ae177232ec2a7 on 2481-alma-numismatics-location** into **b48ac48e8d227c661d38359016160fde4bf44f05 on main**.

I'm curious about indexing `num` in alma during QA, not indexing `rare$num` before alma. because of the timing of the required figgy change. but I won't hold up this PR over it; it sounds like if we wanted to change it it would have to be done here and in requests.
